700352f-a.title: Bronx: 233rd Street (East) - Bronx Boulevard
700352f-a.text:
(1)
East 233rd Street, adjoining the N.W. corner of Bronx Boulevard,
showing the Bronx River Inn. It was built in 1885. The view is in
a westerly direction.
June 6, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, from the opposite direction (viewed eastward), and in-
cluding a 222-story house, No. 597, at the N.W. corner of Bronx
Boulevard.
June 6, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.

700353f-a.title: Bronx: 233rd Street (East) - Bronx Boulevard
700353f-a.text:
East 233rd Street, at, adjoining and east of the N.E. corner of Bronx
Boulevard. The 1-story brick building, at the corner, bears No. 4200 on
the last named thoroughfare, while the two adjoining houses bear Nos.
611 and 613 East 233rd Street.
June 6, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
